
AWS configuration:
    In order to use terraform with AWS, it is necessary to set up your amazon credentials.
        cdm: aws configure
        AWS Access Key ID [None]: [value of the key]
        AWS Secret Access Key [None]: [value of the key]
        Default region name [None]: us-east-1
        Default output format [None]: json


GIT commands:

- It is important to add to the .gitignore file the .terraform/ folder
    since it has large size files which are not supported by GitHub

clone a new repo from GitHub:
    - git clone <ssh_repo_url>

create a new branch:
    - git checkout -b <new_branch_name>

List existing branches
    - git branch -a

Push to an specific branch:
    - git push origin <branch_name>

Delete a branch:
    - git branch -d